				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="triberr_endorsement"></div><div id="attachment_11636" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://cdn.writershelpingwriters.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/birthday-109971_1280.jpg"><img class="wp-image-11636 size-medium" src="http://cdn.writershelpingwriters.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/birthday-109971_1280-300x200.jpg" alt="birthday-109971_1280" width="300" height="200" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Pixabay</p></div>
<p>Happy Birthday, Angela! I am SO glad that you were born on this day only 29 years ago ;). Sleep in, eat some extra chocolate, and take it easy today! And if anyone else would like to congratulate the birthday girl, you can do so here in the comments, on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/AuthorAngelaAckerman/" target="_blank">Facebook</a>, or on her <a href="https://twitter.com/AngelaAckerman" target="_blank">Twitter account</a>.</p>
<p>Now that Christmas is upon us, Angela and I are getting ready to take our annual blog-cation through the end of the year. But because I like to hear myself talk, I need to leave you with a few final words before signing off:</p>
<p>First of all, the 25-page critique contest is now closed. We&#8217;ll be randomly drawing two names after the first of the year and will announce the winners when we return on January 5th. Thanks for entering, everybody! I&#8217;m SO excited to dig into some good reading in the new year.</p>
